datasets.name: 4ff7fd59
datasets.query:
WITH storage_creds_cte AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT storage_credential_name AS access_credential, storage_credential_id AS app_id
  FROM system.information_schema.storage_credentials
),
cte_details AS (
  SELECT
    resources[0].accountId AS accountId,
    bucket,
    table_catalog,
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    full_table_name AS full_namespace,
    storage_path,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    eventtype AS authType,
    requestid AS authObjectId,
    storage_creds_cte.access_credential,
    userAgent,
    CASE WHEN storage_creds_cte.access_credential IS NOT NULL THEN 'databricks' ELSE 'external' END requester,
    operation
  FROM
    access_insights.default.cloudtrail_with_auditevents
    LEFT JOIN storage_creds_cte ON requestid = storage_creds_cte.app_id
)
SELECT
  accountId,
  bucket,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN operation = 'READ' AND requester = 'external' THEN 1 ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS external_read,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN operation = 'READ_WRITE' AND requester = 'external' THEN 1 ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS external_write,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN operation = 'READ' AND requester = 'databricks' THEN 1 ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS uc_read,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN operation = 'READ_WRITE' AND requester = 'databricks' THEN 1 ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS uc_write,
  CASE
    WHEN uc_read > 0 AND uc_write = 0 AND external_read = 0 AND external_write = 0 THEN 'Databricks readers'
    WHEN uc_read = 0 AND uc_write > 0 AND external_read = 0 AND external_write = 0 THEN 'Databricks writers'
    WHEN uc_read > 0 AND uc_write > 0 AND external_read = 0 AND external_write = 0 THEN 'Databricks readers & writers'
    WHEN uc_read >= 0 AND uc_write >= 0 AND external_read > 0 AND external_write = 0 THEN 'Non-Databricks readers'
    WHEN uc_read >= 0 AND uc_write >= 0 AND external_read = 0 AND external_write > 0 THEN 'Non-Databricks writers'
    WHEN uc_read >= 0 AND uc_write >= 0 AND external_read > 0 AND external_write > 0 THEN 'Non-Databricks readers & writers'
    WHEN uc_read = 0 AND uc_write = 0 AND external_read = 0 AND external_write = 0 THEN 'No readers or writers'
  END AS classification
FROM
  cte_details
GROUP BY
  accountId,
  bucket,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format

datasets.name: d39a1e56
datasets.query:
with cte_table_details AS (
  SELECT 
    table_catalog, 
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    storage_path
  FROM system.information_schema.tables
),
cte_tables AS (
  SELECT 
    table_catalog, 
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    concat_ws(".", table_catalog, table_schema, table_name) as full_namespace,
    storage_path,
    concat_ws("/",
      regexp_extract(storage_path, "s3?://([^/]+)@([^.]+)(\.[^/]+)(?:/(.+))?", 2),
      regexp_extract(storage_path, "s3?://([^/]+)@([^.]+)(\.[^/]+)(?:/(.+))?", 1),
      regexp_extract(storage_path, "s3?://([^/]+)@([^.]+)(\.[^/]+)(?:/(.+))?", 4)
    ) as parsed_path,
    table_type,
    data_source_format
  FROM cte_table_details
  WHERE 1=1
    AND table_catalog NOT IN ('system', '__databricks_internal')
    AND storage_path is not null
    AND table_type = 'EXTERNAL'
    -- AND data_source_format = 'DELTA'
),
cte_details AS (
  SELECT 
    coalesce(slog.table_catalog, "unmanaged") as table_catalog,
    coalesce(slog.table_schema, "unmanaged") as table_schema,
    coalesce(slog.table_name, "unmanaged") as table_name,
    coalesce(slog.full_table_name, 'unmanaged') as full_namespace,
    coalesce(slog.table_url) as storage_path,
    coalesce(slog.table_type, 'EXTERNAL') as table_type,
    coalesce(slog.data_source_format, 'DELTA') as data_source_format,
    slog.userAgent as userAgentHeader,
    CASE 
      WHEN lower(slog.userAgent) like '%databricks%' 
          OR lower(slog.userAgent) like '%dbr%' 
          OR lower(slog.userAgent) like '%apn/1.0 unknown%' 
      THEN 'databricks' 
      ELSE 'EXTERNAL' 
    END as requester,
    operation
  FROM access_insights.default.cloudtrail_with_auditevents as slog
  WHERE 1=1 
    AND slog.operation in (
      'READ',
      'READ_WRITE')
  )
  SELECT 
    table_catalog,
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    full_namespace,
    storage_path,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    SUM (CASE WHEN operation = "READ" AND requester = 'external' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as external_read,
    SUM (CASE WHEN operation = "READ_WRITE" AND requester = 'external' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as external_write,
    SUM (CASE WHEN operation = "READ" AND requester = 'databricks' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as uc_read,
    SUM (CASE WHEN operation = "READ_WRITE" AND requester = 'databricks' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as uc_write,
    CASE 
      WHEN external_read > 0 OR external_write > 0 THEN 'More Investigation Needed'
      WHEN external_read = 0 OR external_write = 0 THEN 'Move to Managed'  
    END AS recommendation
  FROM cte_details -- where table_type =="EXTERNAL"
  GROUP BY 
    table_catalog,
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    full_namespace,
    storage_path,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    requester

with cte_table_details AS (
  SELECT 
    table_catalog, 
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    storage_path
  FROM system.information_schema.tables
)
SELECT 
  table_catalog, 
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  concat_ws(".", table_catalog, table_schema, table_name) as full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format
FROM cte_table_details
WHERE 1=1
  AND table_catalog NOT IN ('system', '__databricks_internal')
  AND table_type IN (
    'MANAGED',
    'EXTERNAL'
  )
  AND data_source_format <> 'DELTASHARING'
  AND table_name NOT LIKE '__materialization%'

datasets.name: 837501df
datasets.query:
with audit_events as (
SELECT 
  to_timestamp(slog.eventTime) as storage_time,
  coalesce(slog.table_catalog, 'unmanaged') as table_catalog,
  coalesce(slog.table_schema, 'unmanaged') as table_schema,
  coalesce(slog.table_name, 'unmanaged') as table_name,
  coalesce(slog.full_table_name, 'unmanaged') as full_namespace,
  coalesce(slog.storage_path) as storage_path,
  coalesce(slog.table_type, 'EXTERNAL') as table_type,
  coalesce(slog.data_source_format, 'DELTA') as data_source_format,
  slog.operation,
  slog.eventName,
  slog.sourceIPAddress,
  slog.resources[0].type as authType,
  slog.table_id as authObjectId,
  slog.userAgent as userAgentHeader,
  slog.requestID as clientRequestId,
  slog.userIdentity.accessKeyId as objectKey,
  CASE 
      WHEN lower(slog.userAgent) like '%databricks%' 
          OR lower(slog.userAgent) like '%dbr%' 
          OR lower(slog.userAgent) like '%apn/1.0 unknown%' 
      THEN 'databricks' 
      ELSE 'EXTERNAL' 
    END as requester,
  CASE
    WHEN slog.email = '' THEN 'External'
    ELSE 'internal'
  END as actionType   
FROM access_insights.default.cloudtrail_logs_with_path as slog
WHERE 1=1 
  AND slog.operation in (
    'READ',
    'READ_WRITE')
)
SELECT 
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  authType,
  authObjectId,
  userAgentHeader,
  requester,
  SUM (CASE WHEN operation = 'READ' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as storage_read,
  SUM (CASE WHEN operation = 'READ_WRITE' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as storage_write,
  SUM (CASE WHEN operation = '' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as storage_delete,
  actionType 
FROM audit_events
GROUP BY ALL
;

datasets.name: b76fe4a6
datasets.query:
with audit_events as (SELECT 
    a.*,
    b.*,
  CASE 
      WHEN b.aws_access_key_id IS NOT NULL
      THEN 'databricks' 
      ELSE 'EXTERNAL' 
    END as requester
FROM
    access_insights.default.cloudtrail_logs_with_path a
Left JOIN 
    access_insights.default.joined_audit_information b
ON 
    a.Resource2 = b.storage_path
WHERE  a.Action2 IN ('s3:AssumeRole', 's3:GetObject', 's3:PutObject', 's3:DeleteObject', 's3:ListObjects')),
audit_events_join_filesize as(Select table_details from access_insights.default.gather_hms_details join audit_events on access_insights.default.gather_hms_details.location_uri = audit_events.Resource2)
SELECT 
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  (table_catalog+'.'+table_schema+'.'+table_name) as full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  table_id as authObjectId,
  userAgent,
  requester,
  SUM (CASE WHEN (action2 = 's3:GetObject' or action2 = 's3:AssumeRole' or action2 = 's3:ListObjects') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as storage_read,
  SUM (CASE WHEN action2 = 's3:PutObject' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as storage_write,
  SUM (CASE WHEN action2 = 's3:DeleteObject' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as storage_delete,
  action2
FROM audit_events_join_filesize
GROUP BY ALL 
;

widget.name: 1a1407a3
widget.textbox_spec:
# Table Migration Breakdown

This dashboard provides a high-level overview of both registered and unregistered tables, as well as how these tables are being accessed. External tables that are exclusively read and updated via Databricks Unity Catalog (UC) are ideal candidates for conversion to 'managed' tables. However, tables with external readers and writers require further investigation before being moved to ensure that other business processes are not disrupted.
